courses.learning_outcomes:
The students are expected to acquire the knowledge on:
a. Molecular biology of the Cell;
b. Gametogenesis;
c. Female Reproductive Cycles;
d. Fertilization, early embryogenesis and pre-implantation development;
e. Embryonic development; and
f. Human Birth Defects (congenital malformations).

The students are expected to understand the IVF Laboratory in the aspect of environment, equipment, work flow, staff and common regulations. In addition, they should acquire the knowledge on:
a. Clinical Embryology Laboratory Routing Procedures;
b. Cryo-preservation;
c. Preimplantation Genetic Testing;
d. Other technologies and procedures used by IVF lab;
e. Establishing and maintaining an IVF Laboratory;
f. Trouble shooting; and
g. Future development.

The students are expected to understand the male reproductive system and their function. In addition, they should acquire the knowledge on:
a. Male Infertility and Factors;
b. Male Infertility- Clinical Part (evaluation and treatment);
c. Male Infertility - Andrology Laboratory Evaluation;
d. Sperm processing and selection techniques in an IVF/IVSCI; and
e. Controlling for quality in the Andrology Laboratory.

The students are expected to have critical thinking on the controversies and ethics issues over ART. They include:
a. Embryo culture;
b. Embryo selection;
c. Embryo transfer;
d. Assisted hatching;
e. best development stage for embryo biopsy;
f. Freezing; and
g. Surgical sperm retrieval.

At the conclusion of the course, students should be able to:
1. explain genetic inheritance pattern, risk assessment and ethnicity screening;
2. describe genetic and chromosomal causes of male and female infertility and infertility test options;
3. define genetic and chromosomal test options for recurrent pregnancy-loss patients;
4. outline donor carrier screening guidelines and their application to current practice;
5. evaluate the value of high throughout carrier screening in the ART setting and review current test techniques and applications of PGD.

On completion of Research Project with selected topic, participants should be able to:
1. Carry out a substantial research-based project;
2. Demonstrate competency in the application of research methodologies;
3. Analyze data and synthesize research findings;
4. Synthesize and critically evaluate published information and present it in written format;
5. Report research findings in written and verbal forms; and
6. Use research findings to advance education theory and practice.
